How to use the bubble-help feature of wizard.library V40

Two new functions have to be used:

1.

NAME
	WZ_ControlBubbleHelpA -- control bubble help (V40)

SYNOPSIS

	WZ_ControlBubbleHelpA(surface,tags);
	                       A0      A1

	VOID WZ_ControlBubbleHelpA(APTR surface, struct TagItem *tags);

FUNCTION

	Control the bubble help feature of wizard gadgets. Each gadget must
	must have the help flag set. The window must have at least the
	following IDCMP flags set: IDCMP_GADGETDOWN, IDCMP_INACTIVEWINDOW,
	IDCMP_INTUITICKS and IDCMP_GADGETHELP.

	surface - the wizard surface handle
	
	tags -
	
		CBH_BubbleHelp (BOOL): switch bubble help on/off.
	
	The IDCMP messages must be filtered using WZ_HandleIMessage to
	display and hide the bubble help windows.

SEE
	
	WZ_HandleIMessage


2.

NAME

	WZ_HandleIMessage -- filter IDCMP messages for wizard windows (V40)

SYNOPSIS

	WZ_HandleIMessage(windowhandle, idcmpmsg)
	                      A0            A1
	
	BOOL WZ_HandleIMessage(struct WizardWindowHandle *wwh,
		struct IntuiMessage *idcmpmsg);

FUNCTION

	Filter the IDCMP messages before application use it. Without calling
	that message you will not see any bubble help windows. But you should
	use it anyway to allow future extensions of wizard.library.
	
	wwh - the window handle of the window that received the message.
	
	idcmpmsg - the idcmp message.
	
RESULT

	TRUE if the message was a private message for wizard.library. Don't
	interprete the message but still reply it.
	
	FALSE if the message is an application message.

SEE
	
	WZ_ControlBubbleHelpA
